tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The results show mild erythrocytosis (elevated erythrocytes and hemoglobin) and a markedly increased platelet distribution width, while other parameters are within normal limits. These findings may suggest possible dehydration, early myeloproliferative process, or laboratory variation. Clinical correlation and, if indicated, further hematological evaluation are recommended.
